theorem
(x in ( v + ( Lin { w } ) ) iff (ex a st x = ( v + ( a * w ) )))
proof
thus (x in ( v + ( Lin { w } ) ) implies (ex a st x = ( v + ( a * w ) )))
proof
assume x in ( v + ( Lin { w } ) );
then consider u being (VECTOR of V) such that A1: u in ( Lin { w } ) and A2: x = ( v + u ) by RLSUB_1:63;
(ex a st u = ( a * w )) by A1,CKB9:1;
hence thesis by A2;
end;

given a such that
A3: x = ( v + ( a * w ) );

( a * w ) in ( Lin { w } ) by CKB9:1;
hence thesis by A3,RLSUB_1:63;
end;
